1. satis diu silui] Of Luther’s corre- spondence with Erasmus nothing is extant between May 1519 (Ep. 980) and this date. He wrote to Erasmus in the autumn of 1519 (Ep. 1041. 46n), c. 5 May and c. Nov. 1520 (Epp. 1113 introd„ 1166. 90n); Erasmus to him c. Aug. 1520 (Ep. 1141. 15n).

3. silentia] Cf. Lucr. 4. 583, Vel-g. Aen. 10. 63.

6. Papistas] Of. Ep. 1459. 94n.

8. momorderis] For the depth to which Luther had been stung by many of Erasmus' utterances about him cf.
